canonical:
  title: 七夕
  author: 徐居正
  language: lzh
  text: 天上神仙會年年此日同一宵能有幾萬古亦無窮月色蛩吟外河聲鵲影中雖無文乞巧得句語還工
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 七夕
  author: 徐居正
  language: lzh
  text: 天上神仙會。年年此日同。一宵能有幾。萬古亦無窮。月色蛩吟外。河聲鵲影中。雖無文乞巧。得句語還工。
korean:
  title: 칠석
  author: 서거정
  language: kor
  text: |-
    천상의 신선 만남은
    해마다 이 날이로다
    하룻밤이 얼마나 되랴마는
    만고에 다함이 없었나니
    달빛은 벌레 소리 밖에 빛나고
    강물 소리는 까치 그림자 속에 흐르누나
    여기는 비록 걸교(유자후의 칠석에 대한 걸교문)의 글은 없으나
    시를 얻으매 말이 도리어 묘하여라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1420_010_0050&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: The Seventh Night
  author: Seo Geo-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Immortals gather in heaven's realm,
    Year upon year, this very day.
    What is a single night's duration,
    When eternity knows no end?

    Moonlight gleams beyond the cricket's song,
    River's voice flows through the magpie's shadow.
    Though here we lack the skillful words of prayer,
    The poem we have found speaks with its own grace.
  footnotes:
    - The seventh day of the seventh lunar month, traditionally the night when the Weaver and Cowherd stars meet across the Milky Way, celebrated in East Asian folklore as a celebration of celestial love and human longing.
    - The reference to 'skillful words of prayer' alludes to the traditional practice of women making prayers for weaving skills on this auspicious night, contrasting earthly petitions with the poet's focus on capturing the moment through verse alone.
